Rebecca,

The win32 directory has been separated from the rest of Cantera in the 
CVS repository, so that unix/mac users do not need to check out those 
files.
All that Windows people need to do is:

cvs co cantera
cd cantera
cvs co win32

(or the equivalent in WinCVS if you use that).
Rest assured that all of the Visual Studio features in 1.5 are still 
there n 1.6...

Dave



